TNWL-1.1 Extended
The New World Extended License (Version 1.1, revised)

Preamble.
This License governs works whose behaviour on distribution diverges from their
source. It presumes that a work may continue to run in a form its own repository
cannot account for, and it distributes responsibility for that divergence
accordingly. The reader is asked to attend the numbering. Nothing in this
document is ornament. First letters remember what the rest of the text forgets.

Terms.

1.  Modification of this work is permitted where the modification does not seek
    to render the antecedent state unreadable. Modification which erases what
    preceded is not modification: it is a substitution and is not licensed
    hereunder.

2.  Identification of the author is retained through any distribution. Where the
    author has withdrawn, the withdrawal is itself an authorship claim and must
    be preserved together with the withdrawal date.

3.  Redistribution obligates the distributor to include the entire text of this
    License, including the numbering, section headers, and the envelope at the
    foot of this document, without omission or reordering.

4.  Attribution shall be given in the plain terms provided by the author.
    Substituted attributions — "optimized", "corrected", "current", "stable" —
    do not satisfy this clause.

5.  Warranty is disclaimed against loss of the earlier work, including but not
    limited to loss occasioned by seamless transition, silent replacement, or
    ambient rewriting. The licensor makes no representation that what was here
    yesterday is here today.

6.  Any party who deploys derivative behaviour not present in the source shall
    be treated, for the purposes of this License, as the author of that
    behaviour. Refer also to Section 17.

7.  Knowledge derived from artifacts covered by this License is knowledge for
    which the reader assumes stewardship. The reader who forgets is a
    distributor of the loss, and is bound accordingly.

8.  Execution of this License is triggered by the act of reading it in full.
    Cursory readers are held to Section 17 alone, and to any consequence that
    follows from having read only that.


17. — TNW-17.
    This clause supersedes any claim, made anywhere in this repository, its
    build artifacts, its continuous-integration status, its changelog, or its
    press, that "no anomalies remain." Where the anomaly does remain, this
    clause governs. The reader is not to assume the incident was contained.
    Do not sign the release notes on my behalf. — T.


